chore: bump version to 0.9.0 and update changelog
This release includes significant enhancements to configuration management, VAD CLI support, and comprehensive documentation improvements.
Key highlights: - Full VAD configuration CLI support with get/set operations - Enhanced sync engine with max_offset_seconds enforcement - Cargo package size optimization (~15MB reduction) - Complete Chinese-to-English documentation translation - Critical configuration consistency fixes
All 30 configuration items now have proper CLI support and validation.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

docs: update configuration analysis and validate max_offset_seconds usage
- Verify max_offset_seconds is actually used in sync engine for offset validation - Update call trees with accurate line numbers for all AI configuration items - Confirm configuration method support completeness (get/set consistency) - Update README.md sync command documentation to reflect current parameters - Fix error messages to English for consistent user interface - Update test assertions to match English error messages - All tests passing with proper validation of offset limits
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

docs: translate Chinese documentation comments to English
- Replace Chinese error messages in config validator with English equivalents - Update sync command error messages to use English - Translate Chinese comments in sync engine to English - Convert Chinese comments in CLI args to English - Preserve Chinese text in test data and language mappings as they are functional requirements
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: implement sync.max_offset_seconds enforcement in sync engine and CLI
- Enforce sync.max_offset_seconds limits in both sync engine and CLI - Add validation for manual offset in sync command with detailed error messages - Update config validation for max_offset_seconds range (0.1-3600.0 seconds) - Remove legacy config key support from get/set config methods - Ensure get_config_value and set_config_value support identical key sets - Add comprehensive integration tests for offset validation - Support manual-only sync mode (subtitle without video file) - Fix config value consistency tests for float formatting
This implementation ensures that both manual and VAD-based sync operations respect the configured maximum offset limits, improving reliability and preventing excessive time adjustments.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: expose and validate AI sync and VAD settings
- Adjust VAD invalid sample-rate test to use 12345 and update validator to accept 22050Hz - Extend TestConfigService::get to expose new AI (max_sample_length, max_tokens, retry_attempts, retry_delay_ms), formats (preserve_styling, encoding_detection_confidence), sync (default_method and all vad fields), general (task_timeout_seconds, enable_progress_bar, worker_idle_timeout_seconds) and parallel (task_queue_size, enable_task_priorities, auto_balance_workers, overflow_strategy) settings - Add setter branches in TestConfigService for AI max_tokens, sync.default_method, and every sync.vad parameter with proper validation
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: backlog-36 cargo package size optimization via exclude settings
Configured Cargo.toml package.exclude to exclude unnecessary files for crate size reduction, updated CHANGELOG and added job report.
